cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks for feature extraction, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also presents a mathematical model and convergence theory, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the problem being solved involves sparse coding, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of spiking neural networks for computation suggests a potential application in systems and control (cs.SY).
